<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7819] consider split improvements for stripe compactions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7819</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From discussions in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7667&quot; title=&quot;Support stripe compaction&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7667&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7667&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and in person.&lt;br/&gt;
Files cannot be &quot;just moved&quot; to new regions because of snapshot reliance on that not happening (correct me if I&apos;m wrong).&lt;br/&gt;
However, obviously we don&apos;t need compaction after split if we have files with specific ranges, so we could handle this somehow.&lt;br/&gt;
On the other hand, if you have 6 fixed stripes, and split into 3 and 3, you&apos;d want to go back to 6 stripes, so when you do compaction in one of the 3 you will want special handling to do it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
